(Artificial Intelligence (AI) Overview) Tj
T*
/F1 11 Tf
T*
(Artificial Intelligence \(AI\) refers to the simulation of human intelligence in) Tj
T*
(machines that are programmed to think like humans and mimic their actions. The term) Tj
T*
(may also be applied to any machine that exhibits traits associated with a human mind) Tj
T*
(such as learning and problem-solving.) Tj
T*
T*
(The ideal characteristic of artificial intelligence is its ability to take actions) Tj
T*
(that have the best chance of achieving a specific goal. A subset of artificial) Tj
T*
(intelligence is machine learning, which refers to the concept that computer programs) Tj
T*
(can automatically learn from and adapt to new data without being assisted by humans.) Tj
T*
T*
(AI applications include advanced web search engines, recommendation systems,) Tj
T*
(understanding human speech \(such as Siri and Alexa\), self-driving cars, and) Tj
T*
(generative AI tools \(like ChatGPT\). As machines become increasingly capable, tasks) Tj
T*
(considered to require intelligence are often removed from the definition of AI, a) Tj
T*
(phenomenon known as the AI effect.) Tj
T*
